OL,3,C'I feared l'd be burned alive': Asylum
OL,4,Cseeker in hotel attacked by mob
OL,6,FAli said the hotel staff had warned
OL,7,Fthe asylum seekers ahead of the riot
OL,8,Fnot to go out but that he had not
OL,9,Fexpected such violence.
OL,11,F"We had advance warning about a
OL,12,Fprotest. We didn't take it too
OL,13,Fseriously," he said.
OL,15,F"Our staff said we shouldn't leave the
OL,16,Fhotel, close curtains , don't go out -
OL,17,Fso we thought perhaps it is serious.
OL,19,F"We already have been traumatised by
OL,20,Four own country and we thought the UK
OL,21,Fwas a safe country."
